1
00:00:00,535 --> 00:00:02,403
Melinda: previously
on "ghost whisperer..."
why do your friends shine?

2
00:00:02,471 --> 00:00:04,938
Because they don't have faces.
they're made of light. but they're scared.

3
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:06,306
What are they scared of,
buddy?

4
00:00:06,373 --> 00:00:09,042
Of the shadows.
what kind of shadows are those?

5
00:00:09,110 --> 00:00:11,411
The ones they make
from the parts
that get left behind.

6
00:00:11,479 --> 00:00:13,046
Parts of what?
people.

7
00:00:13,114 --> 00:00:14,547
Broken people.

8
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:17,350
I've been trying
to protect you.

9
00:00:17,418 --> 00:00:19,018
You and melinda.
melinda?

10
00:00:19,086 --> 00:00:20,220
I've said too much.
protect her from what?

11
00:00:20,287 --> 00:00:21,221
Is it the shadows?

12
00:00:21,288 --> 00:00:22,288
Stop asking
so many questions!

13
00:00:22,356 --> 00:00:24,324
Don't ask any
questions at all.

14
00:00:24,391 --> 00:00:28,328
her name's julia miller
and she was a patient.

15
00:00:28,395 --> 00:00:30,597
According to this,
she lives here
at the hospital

16
00:00:30,664 --> 00:00:32,365
Her whole life.

17
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:34,167
No one can know
i'm here.

18
00:00:34,235 --> 00:00:35,668
Why not?
if they find out,

19
00:00:35,736 --> 00:00:38,104
Something bad will happen.
what?

20
00:00:38,172 --> 00:00:40,707
Something really bad.

21
00:01:09,136 --> 00:01:11,638
oh.

22
00:01:11,705 --> 00:01:13,840
You scared me.

23
00:01:13,908 --> 00:01:16,009
That's not easy
to do. um...

24
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:18,178
What are you doing here?

25
00:01:18,245 --> 00:01:19,479
I'm waiting for aiden.

26
00:01:19,547 --> 00:01:21,981
Ok, well,
he's at school.

27
00:01:22,049 --> 00:01:24,217
And you don't
belong here, so...

28
00:01:24,285 --> 00:01:26,186
Have i seen you?
it's his closet,

29
00:01:26,253 --> 00:01:28,221
And he said
i could stay.

30
00:01:28,289 --> 00:01:31,958
Yeah, well,
technically it's my house.

31
00:01:32,026 --> 00:01:35,028
And so i decide
who's staying.

32
00:01:44,538 --> 00:01:45,905
Julia miller.

33
00:01:45,973 --> 00:01:47,073
The girl practically
lived here.

34
00:01:47,141 --> 00:01:48,174
Yeah, i knew she
looked familiar.

35
00:01:48,242 --> 00:01:50,009
She had leukemia?
well, she died last week

36
00:01:50,077 --> 00:01:51,644
Of pneumonia,
and her immune system

37
00:01:51,712 --> 00:01:53,346
Couldn't stand
the cancer treatments.

38
00:01:53,414 --> 00:01:55,582
Isn't she the one
who sent you those creepy
sally stitch emails?

39
00:01:55,649 --> 00:01:58,184
One of the many
reasons i don't
want her near our son.

40
00:01:58,252 --> 00:02:00,386
Ok, but i thought
you said ghosts
made her do it.

41
00:02:00,454 --> 00:02:03,223
Well, 11 is a little old
to still be seeing ghosts.

42
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:04,691
But she was dying.

43
00:02:04,758 --> 00:02:06,226
Maybe she was
sensitive.

44
00:02:06,293 --> 00:02:08,061
No, i don't know
how to explain it.

45
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:09,128
There's just something
not right about her.

46
00:02:09,196 --> 00:02:10,797
Says the woman
who just found out

47
00:02:10,864 --> 00:02:12,265
Her son was
keeping a ghost
in his closet?

48
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:13,900
I have a bad feeling
about this one.

49
00:02:13,968 --> 00:02:16,135
Very bad feeling.

50
00:02:16,203 --> 00:02:19,305
Ok. never
a good sign.

51
00:02:19,373 --> 00:02:20,773
Yeah.

52
00:02:22,676 --> 00:02:24,677
It wasn't really
a secret.

53
00:02:24,745 --> 00:02:26,613
I just didn't
tell you about it.

54
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:29,048
Yet.
ok.

55
00:02:29,116 --> 00:02:30,650
But you know you should
have told us that
julia was here.

56
00:02:30,718 --> 00:02:32,018
Right?

57
00:02:32,086 --> 00:02:33,319
She didn't
want me to.

58
00:02:33,387 --> 00:02:35,355
Well, then you
were keeping
a secret, bud.

59
00:02:35,422 --> 00:02:36,623
That's how it works.

60
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:38,458
We just don't
have secrets
in our home, ok?

61
00:02:38,525 --> 00:02:41,728
Just with other people?

62
00:02:41,795 --> 00:02:44,230
Look, i know
that that can be confusing.

63
00:02:44,298 --> 00:02:45,632
Um...

64
00:02:45,699 --> 00:02:47,267
But it's not--
it's not good

65
00:02:47,334 --> 00:02:48,935
For julia
to be stuck here.

66
00:02:49,003 --> 00:02:52,105
You know? she's supposed
to be in the light
with other ghosts.

67
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:55,241
I'm sorry, mom.
hey.

68
00:02:55,309 --> 00:02:58,211
Maybe you can
convince julia
to talk to mom.

69
00:02:58,279 --> 00:02:59,245
Yeah.

70
00:02:59,313 --> 00:03:01,314
She doesn't like
talking to mom.

71
00:03:01,382 --> 00:03:03,416
Why not?

72
00:03:03,484 --> 00:03:05,585
She says
you don't like her.

73
00:03:05,653 --> 00:03:07,587
Why makes her think that?

74
00:03:07,655 --> 00:03:10,590
'cause you don't
want me to learn
how to do magic.

75
00:03:10,658 --> 00:03:13,226
Oh.

76
00:03:13,294 --> 00:03:16,362
Um, you know,
i just--

77
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:19,599
I just don't like it
when ghosts hide in our house.

78
00:03:19,667 --> 00:03:21,901
Right? but what else
is she doing here?

79
00:03:21,969 --> 00:03:23,970
Besides teaching you
magic tricks?

80
00:03:24,038 --> 00:03:25,705
I don't know.

81
00:03:25,773 --> 00:03:27,940
All she wants
to talk about is magic.

82
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:31,144
Well, why don't you
just promise to tell us

83
00:03:31,245 --> 00:03:32,745
Next time's julia's here, ok?

84
00:03:32,813 --> 00:03:34,213
I love you.

85
00:03:34,248 --> 00:03:35,815
Love you, too.
ok.

86
00:03:35,883 --> 00:03:37,850
Bath time.
i don't want a bath.

87
00:03:37,918 --> 00:03:39,452
Ok. all right.

88
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:42,221
We'll take some of this
into the bed.

89
00:03:58,872 --> 00:04:02,308
Julia, will you please
just talk to me?

90
00:04:02,376 --> 00:04:03,876
Look, i'm not angry
with you.

91
00:04:08,115 --> 00:04:09,916
That is not helping.

93
00:04:37,077 --> 00:04:39,078
What do you want?!

94
00:04:47,888 --> 00:04:49,889
Child, whispering:
can you see us?

95
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:06,469
Sync by honeybunny
www.addic7ed.com

96
00:05:19,010 --> 00:05:20,311
Julia miller?
isn't she the same girl

97
00:05:20,979 --> 00:05:22,646
Who was sending
all those awful emails?

98
00:05:22,714 --> 00:05:24,047
Well, that's why
i'm worried.

99
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:26,849
You know, what
if she's a bad
influence on aiden?

100
00:05:26,917 --> 00:05:29,452
Mel, we do the best we can
to raise our kids.

101
00:05:29,519 --> 00:05:31,187
At some point,
they're going to pick friends

102
00:05:31,255 --> 00:05:32,788
That we wish they hadn't,
you know?

103
00:05:32,856 --> 00:05:33,990
Living or dead.

104
00:05:34,057 --> 00:05:34,991
Don't you remember
that ghost that got ned

105
00:05:35,059 --> 00:05:36,593
To shoplift
from your store?

106
00:05:36,661 --> 00:05:38,595
Exactly, but you didn't
believe me then.

107
00:05:38,663 --> 00:05:40,730
Ok, well, i do now.

108
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:44,100
And i may not have
any advice how to stop
playdates with ghosts,

109
00:05:44,168 --> 00:05:45,869
But i am telling you,
as a mother,

110
00:05:45,937 --> 00:05:46,870
You've got to trust
your instincts.

111
00:05:46,938 --> 00:05:48,205
You've got to cut it off.

112
00:05:48,272 --> 00:05:50,440
Yeah, but what
if she's staying
here for something?

113
00:05:50,508 --> 00:05:52,776
Or i can help her?
cut it off.

114
00:05:58,216 --> 00:06:02,285
Hey. well,
she's here
right now.

115
00:06:02,353 --> 00:06:04,554
Hey, mel, this is
david and linda.

116
00:06:04,622 --> 00:06:05,789
These are julia's
parents.
hi.

117
00:06:05,856 --> 00:06:08,692
Your husband said
that you wanted
to talk to us.

118
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:11,328
Something
about julia?

119
00:06:11,395 --> 00:06:12,362
I'll be nearby.

120
00:06:12,430 --> 00:06:13,363
Thanks.
thank you.

121
00:06:13,431 --> 00:06:14,397
May i?

122
00:06:14,465 --> 00:06:16,900
Sure.

123
00:06:18,302 --> 00:06:20,370
I know about your loss,
and i'm so sorry.

124
00:06:20,438 --> 00:06:22,205
It must be
very difficult for you.

125
00:06:22,273 --> 00:06:23,440
Oh, thank you.

126
00:06:23,507 --> 00:06:24,841
There's some comfort
in knowing

127
00:06:24,909 --> 00:06:26,643
That our daughter's
finally at peace.

128
00:06:27,812 --> 00:06:29,312
I don't know
what jim told you,

129
00:06:29,380 --> 00:06:32,949
And i know that this
is going to sound
a little strange.

130
00:06:33,017 --> 00:06:35,485
But i have a gift.

131
00:06:35,553 --> 00:06:37,354
I can see ghosts.

132
00:06:38,522 --> 00:06:40,657
Have you seen
our julia?

133
00:06:40,725 --> 00:06:41,925
Yes.

134
00:06:41,993 --> 00:06:45,829
She's attached herself
to my 5-year-old son.

135
00:06:45,896 --> 00:06:48,198
Can we talk to her?

136
00:06:48,266 --> 00:06:51,968
She sort of shut us
out of her life
these past few months.

137
00:06:52,036 --> 00:06:53,536
She did?

138
00:06:53,604 --> 00:06:55,972
Yeah. we don't know why.

139
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,841
The doctors say
there may have been

140
00:06:57,908 --> 00:07:00,043
Some psychological issues

141
00:07:00,111 --> 00:07:02,979
That resulted from being
alone in the hospital

142
00:07:03,047 --> 00:07:04,281
For so long.

143
00:07:04,348 --> 00:07:07,183
We weren't even
with her when she died.

144
00:07:07,251 --> 00:07:10,020
Do you think that
maybe why she's still here?

145
00:07:10,087 --> 00:07:11,921
Because she never
got a chance
to say good-bye?

146
00:07:11,989 --> 00:07:13,757
That might be
a part of it,

147
00:07:13,824 --> 00:07:16,026
But i feel like
there's some
unfinished business

148
00:07:16,093 --> 00:07:17,994
That she's just not
telling me about.

149
00:07:18,062 --> 00:07:21,398
What unfinished business
could an 11-year-old have?

150
00:07:21,465 --> 00:07:24,668
You know, we're here to
pick up julia's things.

151
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:26,670
The nurses said that

152
00:07:26,737 --> 00:07:31,207
She did a lot of drawing
and writing.

153
00:07:31,275 --> 00:07:32,909
Well, i guess we could
look at some of those
if you like.

154
00:07:32,977 --> 00:07:34,044
See if we could
find anything.

155
00:07:34,111 --> 00:07:35,211
That would be great.

156
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:36,479
And if you find anything,

157
00:07:36,547 --> 00:07:38,381
Can you just call me?

158
00:07:38,449 --> 00:07:39,516
Thank you.

159
00:07:39,583 --> 00:07:40,917
Thank you.

160
00:07:44,522 --> 00:07:47,624
David: it will be
all right.

161
00:07:47,692 --> 00:07:49,959
But i can still
do magic tricks?

162
00:07:50,027 --> 00:07:53,596
Yeah, as long
as they're not
ghost magic tricks.

163
00:08:02,873 --> 00:08:04,708
Julia, what's going on?

164
00:08:04,775 --> 00:08:07,077
It's none
of your business.

165
00:08:07,144 --> 00:08:10,146
Look, i understand
that this must be
hard for you.

166
00:08:10,214 --> 00:08:11,681
If you just let me,
i can help you.

167
00:08:11,749 --> 00:08:14,117
I need aiden,
not you.

168
00:08:14,185 --> 00:08:16,986
Aiden, go upstairs
and play, ok? right now.

169
00:08:17,054 --> 00:08:19,122
Ok. bye, julia.

170
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:21,591
Right now.

171
00:08:21,659 --> 00:08:23,727
I saw your mom
and dad today.

172
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:25,528
They're very worried
about you.

173
00:08:25,596 --> 00:08:28,298
Look, i get
how confusing
it can be to--

174
00:08:28,366 --> 00:08:30,100
You don't get anything.
you're a grown-up.

175
00:08:30,167 --> 00:08:33,136
Whatever's keeping you here,
i can help you.

176
00:08:33,204 --> 00:08:34,404
Stop saying
you can help me.

177
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:35,638
You can't.

178
00:08:35,706 --> 00:08:37,374
If you just
let me, i can.

179
00:08:37,441 --> 00:08:39,142
Jim: hey?
what's going on here?

180
00:08:39,210 --> 00:08:41,077
Julia's here.

181
00:08:43,781 --> 00:08:44,948
And, uh,

182
00:08:45,015 --> 00:08:46,750
Where is our son,
aiden?

183
00:08:46,817 --> 00:08:49,018
He is upstairs, ok?
and he's playing
and he's fine.

184
00:08:49,086 --> 00:08:50,120
We're just going
to work this out.

185
00:08:50,187 --> 00:08:51,855
No. it's not fine.
no, we're not

186
00:08:51,922 --> 00:08:54,391
Going to work
this out right now.

187
00:08:54,458 --> 00:08:56,559
We're going to put
these knives in here,

188
00:08:56,627 --> 00:08:58,461
And i want julia
out of this house.

189
00:08:58,529 --> 00:09:01,331
Julia, can you hear me?
i want you out of my house

190
00:09:01,399 --> 00:09:04,234
And i want you
to leave my son
alone, got it?

191
00:09:04,301 --> 00:09:05,869
Do you hear me?

192
00:09:05,936 --> 00:09:06,970
Jim...

193
00:09:09,206 --> 00:09:10,540
Does that mean
she's gone?

194
00:09:10,608 --> 00:09:12,175
For now.

195
00:09:12,243 --> 00:09:15,345
You don't know
who you're dealing with.

196
00:09:20,551 --> 00:09:23,820
So, was julia around
last night?

197
00:09:23,888 --> 00:09:26,489
No. i think she's gone.

198
00:09:26,557 --> 00:09:27,824
That's probably
for the best.

199
00:09:27,925 --> 00:09:28,925
You understand that,
right?

200
00:09:28,993 --> 00:09:30,226
Yeah.

201
00:09:30,294 --> 00:09:31,828
Is it ok to miss her?

202
00:09:31,896 --> 00:09:33,396
Of course it is,
sweetie.

203
00:09:33,464 --> 00:09:36,232
Drink your juice,
it's good for you.

204
00:09:38,936 --> 00:09:40,303
oh, my god,
aiden, don't drink that!

205
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:41,771
Aiden!

206
00:10:03,727 --> 00:10:06,162
Aiden?

207
00:10:13,337 --> 00:10:15,338
Aiden!

208
00:10:16,540 --> 00:10:17,474
Aiden!

209
00:10:17,541 --> 00:10:19,476
Jim, i can't find aiden!
hmm?!

210
00:10:19,543 --> 00:10:21,511
Aiden?!

211
00:10:21,579 --> 00:10:23,379
Jim: i'll check
outside!

212
00:10:23,447 --> 00:10:25,949
Aiden!

213
00:10:26,016 --> 00:10:27,417
Baby!

214
00:10:27,485 --> 00:10:29,285
Jim: aiden! aiden!

215
00:10:29,353 --> 00:10:31,354
Aiden, where are you?!

216
00:10:38,195 --> 00:10:39,996
Aiden!

217
00:10:40,064 --> 00:10:42,165
I can't find him
anywhere.

218
00:10:42,233 --> 00:10:44,334
Oh, my god.

219
00:10:44,401 --> 00:10:46,436
Jim, i have searched
every inch of this house.

220
00:10:46,504 --> 00:10:48,505
Honey, honey,
calm down.
it'll be ok.

221
00:10:48,572 --> 00:10:50,740
I'm going to call
the police,
we'll call everyone.

222
00:10:53,878 --> 00:10:56,012
Hello?
9-1-1, what's your emergency?

223
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:58,414
My son is missing!

224
00:11:08,069 --> 00:11:08,769
Melinda, honey.

225
00:11:08,837 --> 00:11:10,671
Have you heard
anything?

226
00:11:10,739 --> 00:11:12,740
No, nothing.
listen, i sent you
a picture.

227
00:11:12,808 --> 00:11:14,709
If you could just
send it to everyone you know.

228
00:11:14,776 --> 00:11:16,077
Ok, sure.

229
00:11:16,178 --> 00:11:17,812
Where's jim?
he's, i don't know,

230
00:11:17,879 --> 00:11:20,081
Driving the neighborhoods,
waking up people.

231
00:11:20,148 --> 00:11:21,549
The police on their way,
and eli, he went straight

232
00:11:21,616 --> 00:11:22,817
To detective blair.
all right.

233
00:11:22,884 --> 00:11:24,151
Well, do you think
it's julia?

234
00:11:24,219 --> 00:11:26,987
She took him. i know it.
the mcallisters, the taubs,

235
00:11:27,055 --> 00:11:28,389
I went as far
as the playground.
nothing.

236
00:11:28,457 --> 00:11:29,857
She's not going to take him
somewhere we've looked.

237
00:11:29,925 --> 00:11:32,560
He's five. technically,
how far can he get?

238
00:11:32,627 --> 00:11:33,894
I mean, can a ghost even
move him like that?

239
00:11:33,962 --> 00:11:35,596
He'd be moving on his own.

240
00:11:35,664 --> 00:11:37,231
Then that means
he's in walking range.

241
00:11:37,299 --> 00:11:39,133
Why is he doing this?
he knows better.

242
00:11:39,201 --> 00:11:40,334
He probably
felt sorry for her.

243
00:11:40,402 --> 00:11:42,002
