00:24:01,339 --> 00:24:03,874
Why isn't there
anyone here?

515
00:24:03,941 --> 00:24:06,309
I thought there'd be
kids here.

516
00:24:06,377 --> 00:24:08,979
Kids love
this place.

517
00:24:09,047 --> 00:24:12,482
It's happy.

518
00:24:12,550 --> 00:24:13,650
Safe.

519
00:24:13,718 --> 00:24:15,519
It's getting dark.

520
00:24:15,586 --> 00:24:17,754
I want to go home.

521
00:24:17,822 --> 00:24:19,356
We can't.

522
00:24:19,424 --> 00:24:20,524
I can't.

523
00:24:20,591 --> 00:24:22,492
We can find a grown-up
and call my mom.

524
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:23,727
She'll send me away.

525
00:24:23,795 --> 00:24:24,828
Just to the light.

526
00:24:24,896 --> 00:24:26,196
You'll like it.
it's nice.

527
00:24:26,264 --> 00:24:27,798
You don't know that.

528
00:24:27,865 --> 00:24:29,366
You don't know anything,

529
00:24:29,434 --> 00:24:31,668
And neither does she.

530
00:24:33,204 --> 00:24:37,741
Why is your voice
sounding mean?

531
00:24:37,809 --> 00:24:39,309
I--i can't go home,

532
00:24:39,377 --> 00:24:41,211
And i can't
go into the light.

533
00:24:41,279 --> 00:24:43,580
If i do,
they'll get hurt.

534
00:24:43,648 --> 00:24:45,382
Who?

535
00:24:45,450 --> 00:24:48,085
All the spirits
that were nice to me.

536
00:24:48,152 --> 00:24:49,419
The good ones.

537
00:24:49,487 --> 00:24:50,620
Ghosts don't get hurt.

538
00:24:50,688 --> 00:24:52,122
My mom says
they can't feel pain.

539
00:24:52,190 --> 00:24:53,523
She's wrong.

540
00:24:53,591 --> 00:24:54,524
We do.

541
00:24:54,592 --> 00:24:56,560
How?

542
00:24:56,627 --> 00:25:00,363
It's an uh-oh feeling.
you know, like when

543
00:25:00,431 --> 00:25:01,732
You've done
something wrong.

544
00:25:01,799 --> 00:25:03,867
It's all you can
think about.

545
00:25:03,935 --> 00:25:06,803
The bad thing you did.

546
00:25:06,871 --> 00:25:08,972
All of the bad things
you did.

547
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:11,675
And it grows
and grows until
that's all you are.

548
00:25:11,743 --> 00:25:13,777
You're nothing else.

549
00:25:13,845 --> 00:25:17,347
It eats you up
completely.

550
00:25:18,983 --> 00:25:21,752
It's coming for me.

551
00:25:21,819 --> 00:25:24,020
I know it.

552
00:25:58,371 --> 00:26:00,873
This is it,
this is it. aiden!

553
00:26:00,940 --> 00:26:02,908
Aiden, can you hear me?

554
00:26:02,976 --> 00:26:04,109
Aiden!

555
00:26:04,177 --> 00:26:05,544
The bus driver
said it was this stop.

556
00:26:05,612 --> 00:26:07,012
Aiden!

557
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:09,581
Aiden, no matter what
julia said,

558
00:26:09,649 --> 00:26:11,183
It's not all right to hide.

559
00:26:11,251 --> 00:26:14,153
Aiden, if you can
hear my voice...

560
00:26:15,288 --> 00:26:16,388
Damn it.

561
00:26:21,828 --> 00:26:23,595
What the hell
is that?

562
00:26:31,871 --> 00:26:33,272
Aiden?!

563
00:26:33,339 --> 00:26:34,740
Aiden!

564
00:26:34,808 --> 00:26:37,042
Aiden, i know
this is yours! aiden!

565
00:26:38,645 --> 00:26:40,846
jim?

566
00:26:40,914 --> 00:26:43,849
Hey! did you find him?
jim: no.

567
00:26:43,917 --> 00:26:46,218
No, but he was here.
he was here by this bus stop.

568
00:26:46,286 --> 00:26:47,853
Look, i just found
a little silver car

569
00:26:47,921 --> 00:26:49,088
That he must have
just dropped.

570
00:26:49,155 --> 00:26:50,989
I called the police.

571
00:26:51,057 --> 00:26:52,324
Are you sure
it's his?

572
00:26:52,392 --> 00:26:54,460
Yeah. because...

573
00:26:54,527 --> 00:26:56,261
It's got the little
scratch on it

574
00:26:56,329 --> 00:26:58,030
Where i showed him how
to use the sliding board
for a jump.

575
00:26:58,098 --> 00:27:02,234
Honey, when we find him,
i swear...

576
00:27:02,302 --> 00:27:03,502
I know.

577
00:27:03,570 --> 00:27:06,205
You're never going
to leave the house again.

578
00:27:06,272 --> 00:27:07,906
Where did you find
the toy?

579
00:27:07,974 --> 00:27:09,374
Just at the edge
of the woods.

580
00:27:09,442 --> 00:27:10,609
He must have been
playing with it

581
00:27:10,677 --> 00:27:11,910
On the bus when
he dropped it.

582
00:27:11,978 --> 00:27:13,412
She probably led him
into the woods.

583
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:15,547
You know, to keep him
out of sight.

584
00:27:15,615 --> 00:27:16,715
All right,
i'm going in there.

585
00:27:16,783 --> 00:27:18,550
Ok, well, just call me
if you see anything.

586
00:27:18,618 --> 00:27:20,686
You know it.
i love you.

587
00:27:20,753 --> 00:27:22,488
I love you, too.

588
00:27:34,601 --> 00:27:36,869
What do the shadows
want with my son?

589
00:27:36,936 --> 00:27:37,970
Carl: i don't know.

590
00:27:38,037 --> 00:27:39,204
I don't
have time, carl!

591
00:27:39,272 --> 00:27:40,472
I'm aware of that, melinda.

592
00:27:40,540 --> 00:27:42,241
No, bedford
just told eli

593
00:27:42,308 --> 00:27:43,842
That they
threatened my son

594
00:27:43,910 --> 00:27:45,711
If i crossed julia
over into the light,

595
00:27:45,778 --> 00:27:47,212
Which means they were
the ones who moved
that furniture.

596
00:27:47,280 --> 00:27:48,447
What i don't
know is why.

597
00:27:48,515 --> 00:27:49,615
I don't know, either,
melinda.

598
00:27:49,682 --> 00:27:50,949
How can you
not know?

599
00:27:51,017 --> 00:27:52,251
What the hell
are you seeing, carl,

600
00:27:52,318 --> 00:27:53,318
When you're doing
all this watching?

601
00:27:53,386 --> 00:27:55,787
Not the shadows.
i told you that.

602
00:27:55,855 --> 00:27:57,956
Ghosts can't see
the shadows.

603
00:27:58,024 --> 00:28:00,859
No one i know sees them,
except...

604
00:28:00,927 --> 00:28:01,860
Aiden.

605
00:28:01,928 --> 00:28:03,428
He sees those others.

606
00:28:03,496 --> 00:28:04,530
The shinies.

607
00:28:04,597 --> 00:28:06,598
And if those beings,
whatever they are,

608
00:28:06,666 --> 00:28:09,635
Fear the shadows,
i'm guessing--

609
00:28:09,702 --> 00:28:12,905
Guessing they co-exist
on the same plane.

610
00:28:12,972 --> 00:28:16,175
Really? carl, that's
the best you can do?

611
00:28:18,545 --> 00:28:20,712
we hear rumors.

612
00:28:20,780 --> 00:28:22,414
We hear whispers.

613
00:28:22,482 --> 00:28:23,682
What?

614
00:28:23,783 --> 00:28:26,685
Whatever they are,
wherever they live,

615
00:28:26,753 --> 00:28:28,887
These shadows
are very interested

616
00:28:28,955 --> 00:28:30,489
In children, melinda.

617
00:28:30,557 --> 00:28:32,691
Especially ghost children.

618
00:28:32,759 --> 00:28:34,293
Why?

619
00:28:34,360 --> 00:28:37,462
No one seems to know.

620
00:28:37,530 --> 00:28:39,831
Are you telling me

621
00:28:39,899 --> 00:28:43,101
That the shadows
want to turn my son
into a ghost?

622
00:28:44,337 --> 00:28:47,706
I told you,
i don't know.

623
00:28:50,944 --> 00:28:52,778
Then at least tell me,

624
00:28:52,845 --> 00:28:54,379
Do you have some idea
where he went?

625
00:28:54,447 --> 00:28:58,116
I can't--i can't.
he's hidden from me.
how?

626
00:28:58,184 --> 00:29:00,886
I can't see clearly.
my vision,

627
00:29:00,954 --> 00:29:04,556
It's filled with pictures
from my past.

628
00:29:04,624 --> 00:29:08,594
Everywhere i look,
it's like an endless
slide show

629
00:29:08,661 --> 00:29:10,529
Of every mistake
i made in my life.

630
00:29:10,597 --> 00:29:12,297
It's like a sickness of guilt.

631
00:29:12,365 --> 00:29:14,266
Is that why
you seem so weak?

632
00:29:15,868 --> 00:29:17,736
Oh.

633
00:29:17,804 --> 00:29:19,972
It's the shadows.

634
00:29:20,039 --> 00:29:21,907
If that's true...

635
00:29:21,975 --> 00:29:24,643
Do everything you can,
melinda,

636
00:29:24,711 --> 00:29:25,811
Not to anger them.

637
00:29:25,878 --> 00:29:28,180
I will do anything
to get my son back.

638
00:29:28,248 --> 00:29:29,581
Just don't anger them.

639
00:29:29,649 --> 00:29:32,818
I will do anything.

640
00:29:32,885 --> 00:29:35,654
hello?

641
00:29:35,722 --> 00:29:37,122
Jim: mel, i just talked
to detective blair.

642
00:29:37,190 --> 00:29:38,690
She's going to send
a search party
up to these woods.

643
00:29:38,758 --> 00:29:39,958
Ok, well,
did you find anything?

644
00:29:40,026 --> 00:29:41,727
It's weird.
i found a little
yellow school bus,

645
00:29:41,794 --> 00:29:43,128
And i'm pretty sure
that it's aiden's.

646
00:29:43,196 --> 00:29:45,430
something else shiny.

647
00:29:45,498 --> 00:29:46,565
What are you getting at?

648
00:29:46,633 --> 00:29:48,667
Last night,
in the kitchen, um,

649
00:29:48,735 --> 00:29:49,868
Everything was shiny.

650
00:29:49,936 --> 00:29:51,370
You know, remember?

651
00:29:51,437 --> 00:29:54,139
Remember, aiden said
that the shadows
and the shinies,

652
00:29:54,207 --> 00:29:55,641
That they hate each other?

653
00:29:55,708 --> 00:29:57,743
Well, what if julia
put all that stuff
out there because

654
00:29:57,810 --> 00:29:59,177
She was trying
to keep the shadows away

655
00:29:59,245 --> 00:30:00,512
And attract the shinies?

656
00:30:00,580 --> 00:30:01,647
Wait, do you think
that's why

657
00:30:01,714 --> 00:30:03,482
They brought
these toys with them?

658
00:30:03,549 --> 00:30:05,117
I don't know,
maybe. carl--

659
00:30:06,252 --> 00:30:07,619
Carl?

660
00:30:09,389 --> 00:30:11,323
Wait a minute. oh!

661
00:30:11,391 --> 00:30:12,924
Melinda,
i found another one.

662
00:30:12,992 --> 00:30:14,293
It's a little
tiny train.

663
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:16,728
He's not dropping
that stuff on accident.

664
00:30:16,796 --> 00:30:18,563
So what do you think,
he's leaving a trail
of bread crumbs?

665
00:30:18,631 --> 00:30:19,731
He's trying to tell us
something.

666
00:30:19,799 --> 00:30:21,466
The car, the bus,
the train--

667
00:30:21,534 --> 00:30:22,668
It all has
to do with travel.

668
00:30:22,735 --> 00:30:24,169
Wait a minute,
travel town.

669
00:30:24,237 --> 00:30:26,104
Remember that place?
it's nearby here.

670
00:30:26,172 --> 00:30:27,873
But it shut down
a couple years ago.

671
00:30:27,940 --> 00:30:29,841
The ghost
wouldn't know that.

672
00:30:29,909 --> 00:30:31,310
She's been in the hospital.

673
00:30:31,377 --> 00:30:34,212
It is right
where i'm headed.

674
00:30:34,280 --> 00:30:35,580
I'll meet you there.

675
00:30:45,124 --> 00:30:47,626
Julia: don't go!
don't leave me!

676
00:30:47,694 --> 00:30:50,062
I want to go home.

677
00:30:50,129 --> 00:30:51,163
There must be a phone,

678
00:30:51,230 --> 00:30:52,898
Or a grown-up
to ask for help.

679
00:30:52,965 --> 00:30:55,834
It's getting too dark.
it's not safe.

680
00:30:55,902 --> 00:30:58,236
This isn't
the train station.

681
00:30:58,304 --> 00:31:00,272
What is it?

682
00:31:00,340 --> 00:31:01,740
It's travel town.

683
00:31:01,808 --> 00:31:04,276
I used to come here
with my parents.

684
00:31:04,344 --> 00:31:06,411
Why didn't you
tell me that?

685
00:31:06,479 --> 00:31:09,414
I didn't want you to know,
or your mom would find out.

686
00:31:09,482 --> 00:31:10,549
How would my mom
find out?

687
00:31:10,616 --> 00:31:13,051
She never told you?

688
00:31:13,119 --> 00:31:14,653
She can see
what you can see.

689
00:31:14,721 --> 00:31:17,789
It's like
she's spying on you.

690
00:31:17,857 --> 00:31:18,890
I've watched her.

691
00:31:18,958 --> 00:31:20,392
She can see it all.

692
00:31:24,464 --> 00:31:26,365
Where you going?

693
00:31:26,432 --> 00:31:28,533
There's a light
over there.

694
00:31:40,613 --> 00:31:43,215
Aiden: hello?

695
00:31:43,282 --> 00:31:44,616
Hello?

696
00:31:46,185 --> 00:31:48,186
I don't
like it here.

697
00:31:48,254 --> 00:31:50,021
I want to go
some place safe.

698
00:31:50,089 --> 00:31:52,491
My mom says
ghosts are safe
in the light.

699
00:31:52,558 --> 00:31:54,693
You should go in the light.

700
00:31:54,761 --> 00:31:55,794
You sill trust her?

701
00:31:55,862 --> 00:31:58,430
After she lied to you?

702
00:31:58,498 --> 00:32:01,400
Just look around
and see if you can
find the light.

703
00:32:01,467 --> 00:32:04,403
It's too dark
in here.

704
00:32:09,909 --> 00:32:12,477
I can feel them.

705
00:32:12,545 --> 00:32:15,280
They're here.

706
00:32:22,889 --> 00:32:24,256
Stay close to me.

707
00:32:24,323 --> 00:32:26,425
Aiden!

708
00:32:26,492 --> 00:32:27,459
I'm scared.

709
00:32:27,527 --> 00:32:30,462
I'm scared,
i'm scared!

710
00:32:30,530 --> 00:32:33,398
I can't see them!
where are they?

711
00:32:33,466 --> 00:32:35,801
Close your eyes.

712
00:32:35,868 --> 00:32:38,570
I'm scared,
i'm scared!

713
00:32:40,306 --> 00:32:41,373
Keep your eyes
closed.

714
00:32:49,849 --> 00:32:51,817
What's happening to me?!

715
00:32:57,690 --> 00:33:00,025
I can still see
everything!

716
00:33:00,092 --> 00:33:01,493
All the bad stuff.

717
00:33:07,733 --> 00:33:11,470
All the bad stuff
i've ever done!

718
00:33:11,537 --> 00:33:13,472
It's everywhere i look!

719
00:33:15,908 --> 00:33:18,910
It's everywhere.

720
00:33:18,978 --> 00:33:20,011
I hate you
for putting me here!

721
00:33:20,079 --> 00:33:22,447
I just want to die!

722
00:33:22,515 --> 00:33:24,983
No!

723
00:33:25,051 --> 00:33:26,885
Aiden: no! please, no!

724
00:33:27,953 --> 00:33:29,654
It eats you up completely.

725
00:33:30,656 --> 00:33:33,725
No! stop!

726
00:33:42,909 --> 00:33:44,477
Aiden, get out.

727
00:33:44,544 --> 00:33:46,147
And your backpack, quick!

728
00:33:48,050 --> 00:33:49,985
Hurry, aiden, hurry!

729
00:34:14,207 --> 00:34:16,108
Where are you?

730
00:34:16,176 --> 00:34:19,344
Come on!

731
00:34:20,113 --> 00:34:21,414
Julia:
what's happening?!

732
00:34:21,481 --> 00:34:22,548
Aiden:
the shinies...

733
00:34:22,616 --> 00:34:24,617
They won't come in.
they're too scared.

734
00:34:24,685 --> 00:34:27,920
The other shadows
are keeping them out!

735
00:34:27,988 --> 00:34:30,823
I need help!

736
00:35:32,486 --> 00:35:33,853
Aiden: are you ok?

737
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:36,989
It was so awful!

738
00:35:44,898 --> 00:35:46,999
Melinda: aiden?
aiden!

739
00:35:47,067 --> 00:35:49,301
Jim: mel!

740
00:35:49,369 --> 00:35:50,836
Aiden!

741
00:35:50,904 --> 00:35:52,204
Mom, dad!

742
00:35:53,540 --> 00:35:55,074
Oh, my god!

743
00:35:56,376 --> 00:35:58,477
My baby!
aiden, are you all right?

744
00:35:58,545 --> 00:36:00,045
Oh, little buddy!
we're so happy to see you!

745
00:36:00,113 --> 00:36:02,014
Oh! honey!

746
00:36:02,082 --> 00:36:03,349
Are you ok?!

747
00:36:03,417 --> 00:36:04,750
Oh, you really
scared me, man.

748
00:36:04,818 --> 00:36:05,918
You really had us scared.

749
00:36:05,986 --> 00:36:07,486
I know. me, too.

750
00:36:07,587 --> 00:36:09,488
Come here.

751
00:36:09,556 --> 00:36:12,925
Oh, what were you thinking,
you crazy kid?

752
00:36:12,993 --> 00:36:15,027
Cop: is he ok?

753
00:36:15,095 --> 00:36:31,076
Jim: hey, officer.
yeah, we got him,
he's ok.

754
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:35,714
Melinda: it's safe
to come out now.

755
00:36:35,782 --> 00:36:37,583
Are you sure?

756
00:36:37,651 --> 00:36:39,885
Aiden says
there's no shadows.

757
00:36:39,953 --> 00:36:42,955
And there's some people
that you need to see.

758
00:36:51,431 --> 00:36:52,932
It's ok.

759
00:36:58,338 --> 00:36:59,705
Mom and dad?

760
00:36:59,773 --> 00:37:01,240
Linda: is she here?

761
00:37:04,010 --> 00:37:05,544
They came to say
good-bye.

762
00:37:05,612 --> 00:37:07,546
It's time
for you to go
into the light.

763
00:37:07,614 --> 00:37:09,048
No, i can't.
i can't do that.

764
00:37:09,115 --> 00:37:10,983
Because you were
told that something
bad would happen

765
00:37:11,051 --> 00:37:12,618
To your ghost
friends if you did.

766
00:37:12,686 --> 00:37:14,954
Did aiden tell you that?

767
00:37:15,021 --> 00:37:17,223
He was worried
about you.

768
00:37:17,290 --> 00:37:19,291
He saw what happened to me.
i know.

769
00:37:19,359 --> 00:37:21,093
But i'm going
to make sure that
your friends are ok.

770
00:37:21,161 --> 00:37:22,127
How?

771
00:37:22,195 --> 00:37:24,396
By getting some help
from my friends.

772
00:37:24,464 --> 00:37:26,432
I want you
to meet them.

773
00:37:29,503 --> 00:37:30,936
Julia: what will you do?

774
00:37:31,004 --> 00:37:33,272
Well, we have
some things
the shadows don't.

775
00:37:33,306 --> 00:37:34,573
We have a book,

776
00:37:34,641 --> 00:37:37,309
And we have lots
of ghost friends
of our own.

777
00:37:37,377 --> 00:37:38,744
